.TH "hgafb_blank" 9 "hgafb_blank" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hgafb_blank \- (un)blank the screen
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hgafb_blank
.BI "(int blank_mode "  ","
.BI "struct fb_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "blank_mode" 12
blanking method to use
.IP "info" 12
unused

Blank the screen if blank_mode != 0, else unblank. 
Implements VESA suspend and powerdown modes on hardware that supports 
disabling hsync/vsync:
\fIblank_mode\fP == 2 means suspend vsync,
\fIblank_mode\fP == 3 means suspend hsync,
\fIblank_mode\fP == 4 means powerdown.
